SIMPLE: spectrophotometry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spectrophotometry
<hw>Spec`tro*pho*tom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The art of comparing, photometrically, the brightness of two
spectra, wave length by wave length; the use of the
spectrophotometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem., Physics)</fld> <def>the art or process of
measuring the degree of absorption of light at different wavelengths by
a chemical substance, by means of a spectrometer or spectrophotometer.
It is a technique for chemical analysis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Spec`tro*pho`to*met"ric</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spectroscope</ent>⟦br⟧
